  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted despite Test Conditions factor achieving only Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3. The single-configuration limitation is mitigated by the high consistency of experimental results across two independent laboratories (CV < 4% for all QoIs) and the direct correspondence of the tested condition to the regulatory submission scenario. All other 12 V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. Project requirements for model accuracy and validation rigor are documented in the design history file and are referenced throughout this assessment narrative; the structured binding to requirement identifiers is managed at the document-management layer consistent with the Minimal profile declaration.",
